            "title": "A aprendizagem da escrita por crian\u00e7as com suportes digitais",
            "abstract": [
                "This book defends the idea that \u201cthe teaching of language requires accepting that subjects are in continuous constitution as they interact with others, in a continuous process of completing themselves through the other and completing the other, because the concepts that are internalized by both they are ways of understanding the world.\u201d  It reveals to us that \u201cthe teaching of writing acts through the development of creations that had the computer and the smartphone as supports had a special meaning for the children in the research carried out, because in addition to learning to elaborate writing acts inserted in the current enunciation it was possible to provide them with a new learning environment \u2013 the digital environment\u201d. It also shows that \u201cbringing to school varieties of both supports and genres that circulate socially always causes beneficial effects, not only for learning formal language knowledge but also for experiencing its socio-enuciative practices\u201d",
                "Este livro defende a ideia de que \u201co ensino da linguagem exige aceitar que os sujeitos est\u00e3o em cont\u00ednua constitui\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e0 medida que interagem com os outros, num processo cont\u00ednuo de se completar pelo outro e completar o outro, pois os conceitos que s\u00e3o internalizados por ambos s\u00e3o formas de compreender o mundo.\u201d  Revela-nos que \u201co ensino de atos de escrita por meio do desenvolvimento de cria\u00e7\u00f5es que tiveram como suportes o computador e o smartphone teve um significado especial para as crian\u00e7as da pesquisa realizada, pois al\u00e9m de elas aprenderem a elaborar atos de escrita inseridos na corrente enunciativa foi poss\u00edvel proporcionar a elas um novo ambiente d aprendizagem \u2013 o ambiente digital\u201d. Mostra, ainda, que \u201ctrazer para a escola variedades tanto de suportes como de g\u00eaneros que circulam socialmente sempre causa efeitos ben\u00e9ficos, n\u00e3o s\u00f3 para a aprendizagem de conhecimentos formais da linguagem como tamb\u00e9m para a viv\u00eancia de suas pr\u00e1ticas s\u00f3cio-enuciativas\u201d"
            ],
